// v0.0.4 review — cast on non-numeric type raises catchable RuntimeError
// NOTE (BUG-NEW-03): error message differs between WT and VM:
//   WT: "##_(##. requires a numeric value, got String(...))"
//   VM: "type error: expected Int or Float, got String"
// Test catches without inspecting _err to pass both modes.

!? {
    x = ##."hello"
    >> x ¶
} :! {
    >> "caught invalid cast" ¶
}
